        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Thumb deformity-alopecia-pigmentation anomaly syndrome is a rare genetic congenital limb malformation syndrome characterized by short stature sparse scalp hair hypoplastic proximally-placed thumbs and skin hyperpigmentation with areas of 'raindrop' depigmentation. Presence of a single upper central incisor has also been reported. There have been no further descriptions in the literature since 1988."
        },
